{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858283243,"sessionID":"ses_286993884ffeFs08ppeth0PjRz","part":{"id":"prt_d7966eaef001WKcA5sonu2hjyA","messageID":"msg_d7966de6f001TlADO84PQvpUat","sessionID":"ses_286993884ffeFs08ppeth0PjRz","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-a8255bda33fe49868cfd3c0181ada99d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Dependencies Setup\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Add Redis client dependency\n20:   - Run: `go get github.com/redis/go-redis/v9@latest`\n21:   - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n22:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Add Valkey client dependency\n25:   - Run: `go get github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go@latest`\n26:   - Update `go.mod` and `go.sum`\n27:   - Verify: `go mod tidy && go mod verify`\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3** Add test dependency (miniredis)\n30:   - Run: `go get github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2@latest`\n31:   - Verify: `go mod tidy`\n32: \n33: - [ ] **T1.4** Verify pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo exists\n34:   - Check: `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` has SandboxInfo struct\n35:   - Verify struct has required fields: Kind, SandboxID, SessionID, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status, LastActivity\n36: \n37: ### Phase 2: Core Interface & Types\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T2.1** Create `pkg/store/doc.go`\n40:   - Add package documentation\n41:   - Describe store module purpose (Redis/Valkey session persistence)\n42:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T2.2** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Interface Definition\n45:   - Define `Store` interface with methods:\n46:     - `Ping(ctx) error`\n47:     - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n48:     - `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n49:     - `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error`\n50:     - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error`\n51:     - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n52:     - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n53:     - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error`\n54:     - `Close() error`\n55:   - Define `ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")`\n56:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n57: \n58: - [ ] **T2.3** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Singleton Pattern\n59:   - Define `initStoreOnce sync.Once`\n60:   - Define `provider Store`\n61:   - Implement `Storage() Store` function\n62:   - Implement `initStore()` function\n63:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n64: \n65: - [ ] **T2.4** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Error Types\n66:   - Define error constants:\n67:     - `ErrNotFound`\n68:     - `ErrNilSandbox`\n69:     - `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n70:     - `ErrEmptySessionID`\n71:     - `ErrInvalidProvider`\n72:     - `ErrPasswordRequired`\n73:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n74: \n75: - [ ] **T2.5** Create `pkg/store/store.go` - Provider Type Constants\n76:   - Define constants:\n77:     - `redisStoreType = \"redis\"`\n78:     - `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"`\n79:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n80: \n81: ### Phase 3: Redis Implementation - Configuration\n82: \n83: - [ ] **T3.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Configuration Function\n84:   - Implement `makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error)`\n85:   - Read `REDIS_ADDR` env var (required)\n86:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD` env var\n87:   - Read `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n88:   - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n89:   - Return `redisv9.Options{Addr, Password}`\n90:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T3.2** Create `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Struct Definition\n93:   - Define `redisStore struct` with fields:\n94:     - `cli *redisv9.Client`\n95:     - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n96:     - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n97:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n98:   - Implement `NewRedisStore(addr, password string) (*redisStore, error)`\n99:   - Create client, set key prefixes\n100:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement helper function `sessionKey(sessionID string) string`\n103:   - Return `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n104:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n105: \n106: ### Phase 4: Redis Implementation - Core Methods\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T4.1** Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` for redisStore\n109:   - Execute `cli.Ping(ctx)`\n110:   - Expect `PONG` response\n111:   - Return error if ping fails\n112:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T4.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n115:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n116:   - Execute `cli.Get(ctx, key)`\n117:   - Handle `redis.Nil` → return `ErrNotFound`\n118:   - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n119:   - Return sandbox and nil on success\n120:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n121: \n122: - [ ] **T4.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 1\n123:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox → return `ErrNilSandbox`\n124:   - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt → return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n125:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n126:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n127:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T4.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore - Part 2 (Pipeline)\n130:   - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n131:   - Execute `SETNX session:{id} <json>` (only create if not exists)\n132:   - Execute `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}`\n133:   - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}`\n134:   - Exec pipeline\n135:   - Return error if SETNX fails (session already exists) or any command fails\n136:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n137: \n138: - [ ] **T4.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for redisStore\n139:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n140:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n141:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n142:   - Execute `SET key value XX` (only if exists)\n143:   - Return error if key doesn't exist\n144:   - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs (expiry, last_activity remain unchanged)\n145:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T4.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for redisStore - Pipeline\n148:   - Create pipeline: `cli.Pipeline()`\n149:   - Execute `DEL session:{id}`\n150:   - Execute `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n151:   - Execute `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n152:   - Exec pipeline\n153:   - Return error if any command fails\n154:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 1\n157:   - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n158:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n159:   - Get list of session IDs from result\n160:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n161: \n162: - [ ] **T4.8** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore - Part 2\n163:   - For each sessionID, execute `GET session:{id}`\n164:   - Pipeline GET requests for efficiency\n165:   - Skip missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n166:   - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n167:   - Return slice of sandboxes\n168:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n169: \n170: - [ ] **T4.9** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for redisStore\n171:   - Same logic as T4.7-T4.8 but use `session:last_activity` ZSET\n172:   - Execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n173:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n174: \n175: - [ ] **T4.10** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for redisStore\n176:   - Validate: reject empty sessionID → return `ErrEmptySessionID`\n177:   - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n178:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n179:   - Check if key exists: `cli.Exists(ctx, key)`\n180:   - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n181:   - Execute `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n182:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n183: \n184: - [ ] **T4.11** Implement `Close() error` for redisStore\n185:   - Execute `cli.Close()`\n186:   - Return error on failure\n187:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n188: \n189: ### Phase 5: Valkey Implementation - Configuration\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.1** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Configuration Function\n192:   - Implement `makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error)`\n193:   - Read `VALKEY_ADDR` env var (required, comma-separated)\n194:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD` env var\n195:   - Read `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` env var (default: true)\n196:   - Read `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` env var (optional)\n197:   - Read `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` env var (optional)\n198:   - Validate: address required, password required unless explicitly disabled\n199:   - Return `valkey.ClientOption` with InitAddress, Password, DisableCache, ForceSingleClient\n200:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.2** Create `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Struct Definition\n203:   - Define `valkeyStore struct` with fields:\n204:     - `cli valkey.Client`\n205:     - `sessionPrefix string` (default: \"session:\")\n206:     - `expiryIndexKey string` (default: \"session:expiry\")\n207:     - `lastActivityIndexKey string` (default: \"session:last_activity\")\n208:   - Implement `NewValkeyStore(addr, password string) (*valkeyStore, error)`\n209:   - Create client using `valkey.NewClient()`, set key prefixes\n210:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n211: \n212: ### Phase 6: Valkey Implementation - Core Methods\n213: \n214: - [ ] **T6.1** Implement `Ping(ctx) error` for valkeyStore\n215:   - Build command: `B().Ping().Build()`\n216:   - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n217:   - Expect `PONG` string response\n218:   - Return error if ping fails\n219:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T6.2** Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n222:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n223:   - Build command: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n224:   - Execute `cli.Do(ctx, cmd)`\n225:   - Check `valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp)` → return `ErrNotFound`\n226:   - Unmarshal JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n227:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.3** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - Validation & JSON\n230:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox → return `ErrNilSandbox`\n231:   - Validate: reject zero ExpiresAt → return `ErrZeroExpiresAt`\n232:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n233:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n234:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n235: \n236: - [ ] **T6.4** Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n237:   - Build commands:\n238:     - `B().Setnx().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` (SETNX)\n239:     - `B().Zadd().Key(expiryIndexKey).Score(float64(expiresAtUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n240:     - `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(nowUnix)).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n241:   - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n242:   - Check SETNX result: if 0, session already exists → error\n243:   - Return error if any command fails\n244:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n245: \n246: - [ ] **T6.5** Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) error` for valkeyStore\n247:   - Validate: reject nil sandbox\n248:   - Marshal sandbox to JSON\n249:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sandbox.SessionID)`\n250:   - Check existence first: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n251:   - If not exists, return error\n252:   - Execute `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()`\n253:   - Note: Does NOT modify ZSETs\n254:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n255: \n256: - [ ] **T6.6** Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID) error` for valkeyStore - DoMulti\n257:   - Build commands:\n258:     - `B().Del().Key(sessionKey(sessionID)).Build()`\n259:     - `B().Zrem().Key(expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n260:     - `B().Zrem().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n261:   - Execute `cli.DoMulti(ctx, cmds...)`\n262:   - Return error if any command fails\n263:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n264: \n265: - [ ] **T6.7** Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n266:   - If `limit <= 0`, return `nil, nil`\n267:   - Build command: `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(strconv.FormatInt(before.Unix(), 10)).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n268:   - Execute and get session IDs\n269:   - Build MGET command: `B().Mget().Keys(sessionKeys...).Build()`\n270:   - Skip missing keys (IsValkeyNil)\n271:   - Unmarshal each JSON to `types.SandboxInfo`\n272:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n273: \n274: - [ ] **T6.8** Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` for valkeyStore\n275:   - Same logic as T6.7 but use `lastActivityIndexKey`\n276:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n277: \n278: - [ ] **T6.9** Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at) error` for valkeyStore\n279:   - Validate: reject empty sessionID\n280:   - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n281:   - Build key: `sessionKey(sessionID)`\n282:   - Check existence: `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n283:   - If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n284:   - Build command: `B().Zadd().Key(lastActivityIndexKey).Score(float64(at.Unix())).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n285:   - Execute command\n286:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n287: \n288: - [ ] **T6.10** Implement `Close() error` for valkeyStore\n289:   - Execute `cli.Close()`\n290:   - Return error on failure\n291:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n292: \n293: ### Phase 7: initStore Implementation\n294: \n295: - [ ] **T7.1** Implement `initStore()` function - Provider Selection\n296:   - Read `STORE_TYPE` env var\n297:   - If \"redis\", call `initRedisStore()`\n298:   - If \"valkey\", call `initValkeyStore()`\n299:   - If empty or other, return `ErrInvalidProvider`\n300:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n301: \n302: - [ ] **T7.2** Implement `initRedisStore()` helper\n303:   - Call `makeRedisOptions()`\n304:   - Create Redis client: `redisv9.NewClient(opts)`\n305:   - Set provider to `&redisStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n306:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n307: \n308: - [ ] **T7.3** Implement `initValkeyStore()` helper\n309:   - Call `makeValkeyOptions()`\n310:   - Create Valkey client: `valkey.NewClient(opts)`\n311:   - Set provider to `&valkeyStore{cli: client, sessionPrefix: \"session:\", expiryIndexKey: \"session:expiry\", lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\"}`\n312:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/store/`\n313: \n314: ### Phase 8: Unit Tests - Redis Store\n315: \n316: - [ ] **T8.1** Create `pkg/store/store_redis_test.go` - Test Setup\n317:   - Create `setupTestRedisStore(t *testing.T) *redisStore` helper\n318:   - Use `miniredis.RunT(t)` for in-memory Redis\n319:   - Create `makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo` helper\n320:   - Verify: `go test ./pkg/store/... -v`\n321: \n322: - [ ] **T8.2** Test `Ping()` f